If the interviewer asks "What do you know about our company?", keep it short (60–90 seconds):

Sample Answer

"From my research, the Institute for Information Industry (III) is one of Taiwan's most respected ICT and digital transformation organizations. It was established in 1979 through collaboration between the government and private sector to support Taiwan's technology and information industry development.

III focuses on four major areas:

Digital Economy and policy research
Software Technology and AI innovation
Cybersecurity and digital trust
Digital Transformation for industries and government

I understand that III not only conducts advanced technology research but also helps enterprises adopt digital technologies, develops ICT talent, and supports Taiwan's digital ecosystem. What impressed me most is its role as a bridge between technology, industry, and government, helping organizations transform through innovation."

Ultra-Short Version (30 seconds)

"III is a leading Taiwanese ICT and digital transformation organization founded in 1979. It focuses on software technology, AI, cybersecurity, digital economy, and helping industries adopt digital transformation. I am particularly interested in its strong contribution to innovation, talent development, and supporting Taiwan's technology ecosystem."

5 Key Points to Remember

✅ Founded in 1979

✅ Around 2,000 employees

✅ Leading Taiwan's Digital Transformation

✅ Strong focus on AI, Software Engineering, Cybersecurity, and Digital Economy

✅ Acts as a bridge between Government, Industry, and Technology

Why do you want to join III?

"III's mission aligns well with my interest in technology, innovation, and digital transformation. I believe my technical background and project coordination experience can contribute to cross-functional projects while giving me opportunities to learn from industry experts and work on impactful initiatives that benefit Taiwan's digital ecosystem."
